                            <comment id="12876357" author="stack" created="Mon, 7 Jun 2010 18:43:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is the &apos;vnd.&apos; prefix like &apos;x-&apos;?  I seem to be missing how this versions the interface.  Where is the version number in the above?  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12876361" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 7 Jun 2010 18:56:11 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Is the &apos;vnd.&apos; prefix like &apos;x-&apos;?&#160; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;vnd.foo+type is a common convention for vendor specific content types, like x-. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I seem to be missing how this versions the interface.&#160; Where is the version number in the above?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not a version per se, but an alternate and newer representation type. So the current set of media types will correspond to &quot;version 1&quot; and the new media types will correspond to &quot;version 2&quot;. At the next major release, support for both sets of types will collapse to just &quot;version 2&quot;. If we ever have to do this again, we can use the &quot;vnd.foo+type&quot; media types to select &quot;version 3&quot; etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But anyway we can actually provide numeric versioning like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;vnd.hbase.vN+type&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and so why not if that would possibly reduce confusion.&lt;/p&gt;





</comment>
                            <comment id="13689981" author="toffer" created="Fri, 21 Jun 2013 02:38:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reviving this jira. Can we just add version to the path? ie v1/ v2/? This is the standard we use, oozie uses the same scheme as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13690002" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 21 Jun 2013 04:00:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, /v1/... or /v2/...  Those are valid table names, so there&apos;s a backwards compatibility complication. Changing the MIME types as described is unambiguous. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, if you have a patch please consider putting it up so we can take a look at it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
